        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  To normalize txt-like documents (.xml) into .txt format by simple file copy (preserving original), enabling downstream text readers to consume them with a uniform extension. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Txt-like document format normalization via file copy. \par \b Input\/ \:  Files with txt-like extensions (e.g. .xml). \par \b Output\/ \:  Converted .txt file path. \par \b Links\/ \:  [USES_API(6): shutil.copy; READS_DATA_FROM(7): <ref refid="namespacededoc_1_1extensions_1aac3b199243c8795f127aefef6c73fa04" kindref="member">dedoc.extensions.converted_extensions</ref>] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>convert() always copies the file (original preserved).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Output file path is always {dir}/{name_wo_ext}.txt. \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why copy instead of rename? A: Preserving the original file avoids breaking upstream references and supports idempotent operation. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 — Added semantic markup and LDD logging] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
<para>CLASS 7[Converts txt-like formats to TXT via file copy] =&gt; TxtConverter \par \b Use Cases\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>[TxtConverter.convert]: User (Upload) → NormalizeToTxt → TxtFileReady </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
